1) System prep (one-time)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y python3-pip python3-venv tmux git
mkdir -p ~/apps/mybot && cd ~/apps/mybot
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install --upgrade pip
# Your libs (adjust versions if you need)
pip install python-telegram-bot==21.* telethon pyrogram tgcrypto python-dotenv

2) Quick tmux run (your style)

Your sequence, but productionized:

# start a named tmux session
tmux new -s mybot
# inside tmux:
cd ~/apps/mybot
source .venv/bin/activate
python3 your_script.py
# detach (keeps running):  Ctrl+b  then  d


* HOW TO STOP SESSION *


If you started it with tmux

SSH back into your VPS, then list sessions:- 

tmux ls


Kill just the mybot session (recommended):- 

tmux kill-session -t mybot


That immediately stops everything running inside that tmux session (your bot + any loop like run_bot.sh).

( Alternatives )

Kill all tmux sessions: -

tmux kill-server


If you prefer to attach and stop manually: -

tmux attach -t mybot
# inside: press Ctrl+C to stop python, then type:  exit
